Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto, in a line grid, in black ink the upper part of a male figure, accompanied by some titles of a priest of Amun-Ra and a vizier in hieroglyphs. On the verso an incomplete and clumsy sketch in black of a walking male figure, probably a priest, wearing a panther skin.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393930) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393930)
